              </table><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><b><span>反馈训练</span></b><b><span>1</span></b></p><p><span>一．给括号内的单词加上适当的前缀，并用其适当形式填空。</span><span></span></p><p><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Tired and ___________ (courage), he finally gave up.(2009 </span><span>湖南</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>His intelligence and wisdom make up for his _____________ (advantage).</span></p><p><span><span>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Three hours passing by, I became more and more __________ (patient).(2009</span><span>重庆</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>As we know, the Olympic Games is a(n) __________ (national ) sports event.</span></p><p><span><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Driving too fast through city streets is very __________________ (responsible) and dangerous.</span></p><p><span><span>6.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Amazingly, the people were still able to pack into the already ________________ (crowded) bus.</span></p><p><span><span>7.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Some families go without medical treatment because of their _______________ (ability) to pay.</span></p><p><span>8. ---I want to fly straight to London.</span></p><p><span><span>&nbsp; </span>---OK. We have a(n) __________ (stop) flight leaving at 9:25.</span></p><p><span><span>9.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>The news was so __________(expect) that I caught my breath from shock.</span></p><p><span><span>10.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>We can only show mercy to the __________ (fortunate) man. (2005 </span><span>重庆完形填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>11. “I am sorry,” I said, “ I ___________ (take ) you for a Grade Four boy.” (2007 </span><span>江西</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>12. It is not _____________ (common) for students to have difficulty understanding classics.</span></p><p><span>13. It was _____________ (believable) that the fans waited outside the gym for three hours just to have a look at the sports stars.(2005 </span><span>上海</span><span> </span><span>单选填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>14.</span><span> A great scientific ___________ (cover) or a great work of art is surely the result of problem-solving activity. <span>&nbsp;</span>(2005 </span><span>天津阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>15.</span><span> Unlike her 1995 __________ (biography), <i>After All,</i> her second book is less about life as an award-winning actress and more about living with diabetes (</span><span>糖尿病</span><span>).(2010 </span><span>湖南阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>二．根据所给汉语或所缺单词的首字母，写出单词的正确形式。</span><span></span></p><p><span>1. She r ____________________ me that I hadn’t written to Mother. (2010 </span><span>全国</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>2. I had the m_____________ to share a room with someone who snored loudly.</span></p><p><span>3. I’d<b> </b>rather say Mars is totally __________ (</span><span>不适合</span><span>) for human existence.</span></p><p><span>4. Decide what is worth struggling for and let go of __________ (</span><span>不重要的</span><span>) things.</span></p><p><span>5. The film itselt is really an e___________ achievement and quite a feast for the eyes and ears.</span></p><p><span>6. Joan then realized that she had m__________ the woman’s actions--- she wasn’t crazy.</span></p><p><span>7. Many people are __________ (</span><span>察觉不到</span><span>) of just how much food and drink they consume.</span></p><p><span>8. If I find someone who looks like the suspect, my immediate r__________ will be to tell the police.</span></p><p><span>9. Where __________ (</span><span>失业</span><span>) and crime are high, it can be assumed that the latter is due to the former.(2009 </span><span>江苏</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>10. Her father look nervous and ___________ (</span><span>不舒服</span><span>) in front of the cameras.</span></p><p><span>11. There are many others besides me who d__________ with what you say.</span></p><p><span>12. I’m sorry to i__________ , but there’s something important I have to tell you.</span></p><p><span>13. Working with gardeners ___________ (</span><span>使</span><span>……</span><span>能够</span><span>) us to learn a lot of knowledge about flowers. (2007</span><span>上海春</span><span> </span><span>句子翻译改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>14. Journalists will be able to ___________ (</span><span>预览</span><span>) the exhibition tomorrow.</span></p><p><span>15. Population experts p__________ that most people will live in cities in the near futute.</span></p>&nbsp;<p><b><span>常用后缀</span></b><b><span></span></b></p><p><span>后缀（</span><span>suffix</span><span>）是添加到一个单词后面的那一部分，如在单词</span><span>kindness, quickly</span><span>中的</span><span> <span>Cness</span></span><span>和</span><span>-ly</span><span>。英语中的后缀（否定后缀除外）一般对单词本身的含义改变不大，但会改变词性。不同的词类有相对固定的后缀形式，比如，</span><span>-ness</span><span>属于名词后缀，而</span><span>-less</span><span>则属于形容词后缀。所以掌握后缀知识可帮助同学们记忆单词和转换不同的词性，从而提高单词使用的准确性和有效性。根据常见的后缀的特点，我们把后缀分成四类：</span><span> </span><span>名词后缀、形容词后缀、动词后缀和副词后缀。</span><span></span></p><p><b><span>1.</span></b><b><span>名词后缀</span></b><b><span></span></b></p>
