              </table><p><b><span>反馈训练2</span></b></p><p><span>一．给括号内的单词加上适当的后缀，并用其适当的形式填空。</span><span></span></p><p><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Sdyney wants to become a ___________ (law) in the future. (2009</span><span>陕西</span><span> </span><span>单词拼写改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>I went to consult with my __________ (account) before making the decision.</span></p><p><span>3.<span>&nbsp; </span>Coral is not a plant but a _______ (vary) of animal life.</span><span></span></p><p><span><span>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>The __________ (engine) have been accused of having an outlook (</span><span>观点</span><span>) which is too narrowly technical.</span></p><p><span><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>To be effective in school systems, students, teachers, as well as __________ (library), require training.</span></p><p><span><span>6.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Mary’s Christmas cards were listed in the alphabetical order of the family names of the __________ (receive).</span></p><p><span><span>7.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Without mental focus, we may not pay enough __________ (attend) to new information coming in, so it never makes it into our memory stores.</span><span> </span><span>(2010</span><span>浙江阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>8.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Because of his special experience, he was chosen to be an ____________ (assist) to the president for energy affairs. (2010 </span><span>全国单词拼写改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>9.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Many factors have influenced American pronunciation since the first __________ (settle) arrived four hundred years ago. (</span><span>外研教材</span><span>)</span></p><p><span><span>10.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>But if you want to be a __________ (lead), you must learn to fail---and not die a thousand deaths. (2005</span><span>广东</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>11. There are 55_______ (minor) in our country.</span></p><p><span>12. At ________ (long) the bus arrived , forty minutes late.</span></p><p><span>13. Do you know anyone with a mental or physical________ (disable)?</span></p><p><span>14. The ________ (difficult) is how I’m going to understand it without a dictionary.</span></p><p><span>15. Water, food, and _________ (electric) were hard to get. People began to wonder how long the disaster would last.</span></p><p><span>16. The present situation is very complex, so I think it will take me some time to figure out its ________ (real). (2008</span><span>湖北</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>17. In order to avoid __________ (marry), she says that any potential husband must answer three riddles correctly or die.</span></p><p><span>18. Family experts warn that the new ___________ (equal) can also result in less respect for parents.</span><span>（</span><span>2008</span><span>广东</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编）</span><span></span></p><p><span>19. There is a ___________ (possible) that it will be very cold tonight.</span></p><p><span>20. Foortprints are one of the few pieces of hard evidence supporting the _______ (exist) of Yeti (</span><span>雪人</span><span>).</span></p><p><span>21. Make an _________ (arrange). Let’s meet at 6:30, outside the cinema.</span></p><p><span>22. Perhaps their ___________ (fail) is because of their low EQ.</span></p><p><span>23. Staying calm will greatly increase your chances of ________ (survive). (2006</span><span>天津</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>24. In __________ (add) to his movie work, Redford is known as a champion of the environmental causes.</span></p><p><span>25. My parents were in a huge ______ (argue), and I was really upset about it. (2005 </span><span>重庆</span><span> </span><span>阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>26. How do you deal with the _________ (disagree) between the company and the customers?</span></p><p><span>27. It is said that the early European playingCcards were designed for ________ (entertain) and education. (2006 </span><span>辽宁</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>28. There is no special _______ (require) for you to start your ______ (member).</span></p><p><span>29. Mum says I had better pass my exams, or she will sell the computer as ________ (punish).</span></p><p><span>30. The first thing you will read is a ________ (state) of what the argument is about.</span></p><p><span>31. It was their twenty-fifth ________ (wed) anniversary last week.</span></p><p><span>32. The survey found that men got greater _________ (satisfy) from caring for their families than from work.</span></p><p><span>33. I can say nothing--- the matter is still under _________ (discuss).</span></p><p><span>34. This law provides _______ (protect) for threatened animals and plants.</span></p><p><span>35. He gave up his _______ (occupy) as a farmer and became a teacher.</span></p><p><span>36. The English version is boring -----perhaps it has lost something in ________ (translate).</span></p><p><span>37. We have received ______ (inform) that Grant may have left the country.</span></p><p><span>38. I came with every _______ (intend) of staying, but now I’ve decided to leave.</span></p><p><span>39. Some butterflies mix their ________ (surround) so that it’s difficult to see them.</span></p><p><span>40. Once they decide which college to go to, students should reach the _________ (admit) procedures.</span></p><p><span>二．根据所给汉语或所缺单词的首字母，写出单词的正确形式。</span><span></span></p><p><span>1. If you get 11 points, what kind of __________ (</span><span>个性</span><span>) do you have?</span></p><p><span>2. There was a s__________ of oxygen at the top of the mountain.</span></p><p><span>3. The __________ (</span><span>大多数</span><span>) of people in my neighbourhood are Italian.</span></p><p><span>4.I had all my friends around me and the encouragement and g__________ from my family.</span></p><p><span>5. Of course for each item sold eBay get a ____________ (</span><span>提成比例</span><span>) and that is a great deal of money.</span></p><p><span>6. What struck me most was that many of them did not seem particularly happy about their newly found __________ (</span><span>自由</span><span>).</span><span>（</span><span>2008</span><span>湖北</span><span> </span><span>听力改编）</span><span></span></p><p><span>7. Mr Bean, an internationally recognized comedy character on TV and films, amuses audiences regardless of their n__________ or culture.</span></p><p><span>8. Although it is impossible to choose the most important ___________ (</span><span>发现</span><span>), it is possible to single out a few pioneers of the 20th century.</span></p><p><span>9. There is an old proverb, “Love me, love my dog.’’<span>&nbsp; </span>But there is more ___________ (</span><span>智慧</span><span>) in this: “Love me, love my book.’’</span><span>（</span><span>2007</span><span>湖南</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编）</span><span></span></p><p><span>10. King Lear divided his __________ (</span><span>王国</span><span>) into three parts with the intention of leaving them to his three daughters.</span></p><p><span>11. Every few years, the coal workers have their lungs X-rayed to ensure their h__________. (2010</span><span>上海单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>12. Little did Rose care about her own s__________, though she was in great danger herself. (2009</span><span>陕西</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>13.He caught a high fever. His body t___________ was as high as 40</span><span>℃</span><span>. (2007</span><span>浙江</span><span> </span><span>单词拼写改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>14. He claims to have seen a round black ___________ (</span><span>生物</span><span>) moving quickly through the water. (</span><span>外研社教材</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>15. A commercial ____________ (</span><span>广告</span><span>) is one which someone has paid for to promote a product or service.</span></p><p><span>16. That infamous (</span><span>无耻的</span><span>) c___________ was finally sentenced to death.</span></p><p><span>17. She was the teacher who taught us English ___________ (</span><span>文学</span><span>).</span></p><p><span>18. We came up with several choices such as going boating, climbing a mountain, and going to an a__________ park.</span></p><p><span>19. Some died or returned home, but most remained in California to make a life for themselves despite great h__________. (</span><span>人教社教材</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>20. Something as simple as drinking some cold water may clear your mind and relieve __________(</span><span>压力</span><span>).</span><span>（</span><span>2008</span><span>上海单项填空改编）</span><span></span></p><p><span>21. Different cultures emphasize the importance of __________ (</span><span>关系</span><span>) building to a greater or lesser degreee.</span></p><p><span>22. I think we should be cautious and use good j__________ when making decisions.</span></p><p><span>23. Her tennis is much better since she has a new i__________.</span></p><p><span>24. The d__________ drew out the bad tooth from the patient’s mouth.</span></p><p><span>25. The concert features dancers, singers and m__________ of all nationalities.</span></p><p><span>26. That beach is very popular with t__________ because it is long and sandy.</span></p><p><span>27. The orchestra were all in position, waiting for the c__________.</span></p><p><span>28. Confucius was not only a great e__________ but also a well-known thinker.</span></p><p><span>29.<span> </span>Out of __________ (</span><span>好奇</span><span>) , Broad spent hours at the local <span>archives</span></span><span>（</span><span>档案馆</span><span>）</span><span>in a fruitless search for information on McKay.<span> </span>(2009 </span><span>湖南阅读改编</span><span>)</span></p><p><span>30. The youngest sister, Anne, was also a gifted n__________, and her books have the same extraordinary quality as her sisters’.</span></p><p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p></span></span>
