          <p><b><span>反馈训练</span></b><b><span>3</span></b></p>
          <p><span>一．</span><span> </span><span>根据所给汉语或所缺单词的首字母，写出单词的正确形式。</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span>1. The old man passed on his knowledge of ----t__________ Chinese medicine to the younger generation.</span></p>
          <p><span>2. All of them try to use the power of the workstation to present information in a more __________ (</span><span>有效的</span><span>) way. (2009</span><span>北京</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span>3. ―How are your recent trip to Sichuan?</span></p>
          <p><span><span>&nbsp; </span>―I’ve never had a more ___________ (</span><span>宜人的</span><span>) one before.</span><span>（</span><span>2011 </span><span>四川单选改编）</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span>4. I know you’ve been trained as a teacher, but do you have any p__________ teaching experience?</span></p>
          <p><span>5. </span><span>Intellectual property (IP) rights protect an artist from having his/her c__________ ideas copied by another. (2008 </span><span>江西阅读理解改编</span><span>)</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span>6. The mobile phone is f__________in style and convenient to carry, so it is very popular with youngsters.</span></p>
          <p><span>7. Parents gave the school __________ (</span><span>有价值的</span><span>) support in getting its facilities improved.</span></p>
          <p><span>8. My mother doesn’t like me wearing short skirts to church------she doesn’t think they’re s__________.</span></p>
          <p><span>9. Scientists are convinced of the __________ (</span><span>积极的</span><span>) effect of laughter on physical and mental health.</span></p>
          <p><span>10. </span><span>Be _____ (</span><span>讲道理的</span><span>) ―you can’t expect me to finish all this work in so little time. (2012 </span><span>山东单选改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span>11. The Yeti is about two meters tall and has________ (</span><span>强有力的</span><span>) arms and legs.</span></p>
          <p><span>12. Such knowledge is still_________ (</span><span>有用</span><span>) when applied to similar situations in other countries.</span></p>
          <p><span>13.</span><span> ―Can you lend me the book <i>Gone with the Wind?</i></span></p>
          <p><span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp; </span>―Sorry. I returned it to the library just now. Maybe it is still _____. (2012 </span><span>福建</span><span> </span><span>单选改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span>14. The speaker gave us a h_________ joke, which suddenly clicked with us and we all laughed.</span></p>
          <p><span>15. All the houses of the little ________ (</span><span>山区的</span><span>) village were in the shade of grape vines (</span><span>葡萄藤</span><span>).</span></p>
          <p><span>16. Can you tell the difference between _________ (</span><span>有毒的</span><span>) mushrooms and edible varieties.</span></p>
          <p><span>17. Would you please look through the paper for me and see if there are any ________ (</span><span>明显的</span><span>) mistakes?</span></p>
          <p><span>18. Painted by Leonardo da Vinci in the years 1503-1506, the Mona Lisa is a ________ (</span><span>神秘的</span><span>) masterpiece.</span></p>
          <p><span>19. After he became _______ (</span><span>神志清醒</span><span>)</span><span>，</span><span>he remembered having been attacked and hit on the head with a rod.</span></p>
          <p><span>20. She has tried her best. Please don’t be too __________</span><span>（挑剔的）</span><span>about her job. </span><span>（</span><span>2011</span><span>江西单选改编）</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span>21. He was angry with himself for having made such a f__________mistake.</span></p>
          <p><span>22. A s__________person always thinks about himself.</span></p>
          <p><span>23. She was always __________ (</span><span>悲观的</span><span>), even when things were at their best.</span></p>
          <p><span>24. The foreign visitors are going to travel in some__________ (</span><span>南方的</span><span>) provinces of China.</span></p>
          <p><span>25. People in the__________ (</span><span>东部的</span><span>) cities thought they faced a serious coal famine (</span><span>缺乏</span><span>).</span></p>
          <p><span>26. He feels s__________. He shouldn’t have stayed up last night, writing the essay.</span></p>
          <p><span>27. If you cannot find wooden boxes, you may use either__________ (</span><span>塑料的</span><span>) or metal ones instead.</span><span>（</span><span>2009 </span><span>陕西）</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span>28. What I do is to relate my teaching to __________ (</span><span>当代的</span><span>) events in a way that one hasn’t traditionally done.</span></p>
          <p><span>二．给括号内的单词加上适当的后缀，并用适当形式填空。</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Still, despite that handicap (</span><span>不足</span><span>), you’ve made an __________ (admire) Foreign Service officer.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>If you tell him what happened, I’m sure he’ll understand-----he’s a ________ (reason) man.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>That was an __________ (impress) performance from such a young tennis player.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>I must look like the ________ (type) tourist with my shorts and my camera.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>With the development of modern__________ (electric) engineering, we can transmit (</span><span>输送</span><span>) power to wherever it is needed.</span></p>
          <p><span>6. It is not socially ________ (accept) for parents to leave children unattended at that age. (2007 </span><span>山东单选改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span>7. I think this was perhaps the most __________ (enjoy) occasion we had ever had at the White House.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Due to the global warming the forest is producing __________ (addition) tons of wood each year.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>So far we have done a lot to build a low-carbon _________ (economic), but it is far from ideal.We have to work still harder. (2010 </span><span>江苏</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span><span>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>When he turned __________ (profession) at the age of 11, Mike was expected to become a world champion by his coach and parents.</span><span>（</span><span>2006 </span><span>上海</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编）</span><span></span></p>
          <p><span><span>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>We were astonished to find the temple still in its __________ (origin) condition.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>My doctor said the problem was more _________ (emotion) than physical.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>6.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>My ankle is still too_________ (pain) to walk on.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>7.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>I like a place that is________ (peace) and quiet and far from everything.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>8.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>You will be________ (success) in the interview once you have confidence. (2007 </span><span>福建</span><span> </span><span>单项填空改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span><span>9.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Practicing is ________ (tire), but stick with it and some day you will be a good pianist.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>10.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Her neck has been _________ (trouble) for quite a while, and she will probably need surgery on it.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>11.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Many things such as tobaco, fat, sugar, and other polluted things are ________ (harm) to our hearts.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>12.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>It is hard to stay happy and _________ (cheer) when you are ill, or when you are old or your body aches.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>13.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>I wanted to withdraw 40 from our bank account, but I’m so ___________ (forget) that I couldn’t remember if 40 was spelled “fourty”or “forty”.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>14.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Not knowing how to use a computer makes it more difficult for him to do his__________ (academy) research.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>15.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Barack Obama’s victory is a __________ (history) victory that promised change and overcame centuries’ prejudice.</span></p>
          <p><span><span>16.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>Do you intend to go to the town by the __________ (north) route?</span></p>
          <p><span>24. Compared with his sister, Jerry is even more________</span><span>（</span><span>sense</span><span>）</span><span>to, and more easily troubled by, emotional and relationship problems. (2009 </span><span>山东单选改编</span><span>)</span></p>
          <p><span><span>25.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span>The performance left me__________ (breath) with excitement.</span></p>
          <p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
          <p><span><span>&nbsp;<img src="http://mat1.qq.com/gongyi/images/gongyi_icon.gif" data="http://a1.qpic.cn/psb?/V13J4ju20j2Xxv/5S85LDleq2kcxJ2wD9VnFcww9adXH88*sD0QRM16hMI!/b/dEElkMP0FwAA&amp;ek=1&amp;kp=1&amp;pt=0&amp;bo=9gIgAwAAAAABAPA!&amp;su=020526337&amp;tm=1490558400&amp;sce=0-12-12&amp;rf=2-9" /></span></span><b><span><br /><span>&nbsp;3.&nbsp;副词后缀（详情看书）<br /><span>&nbsp;4. 动词后缀&nbsp;（详情看书）<br /><span>&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;词缀（前后缀）过关验收 ---从单句到语篇全方位验收（详情看书）&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></b></p>
          <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span>&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</span></p>
          <p><b><span>名词反馈训练2</span></b><b><span>答案</span></b></p>
          <p><b><span>一．</span></b><span>lawyer<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>2. accountant<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>3. variation<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>4. Engineers<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>5. librarians<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>6. receivers<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>7. attention<span>&nbsp; </span>8. assistant<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>9. settlers <span>&nbsp;</span>10. leader<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>11. minorities<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>12. length<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>13. disability<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>14. difficulty<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>15. electricity<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>16. reality<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>17. marriage<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>18. equality<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>19. possibility<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>20. existence<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>21. arrangement<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>22. failure<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>23. survival<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>24. addition<span>&nbsp; </span>25. argument<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>26. disagreement<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>27. entertainment<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>28. requirement, membership<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>29.punishment<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>30. statement<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>31. wedding 32. satisfaction<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>33. discussion<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>34. protection<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>35. occupation<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>36. translation<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>37. information<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>38. intention<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>39. surroundings<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>40. admission<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>
          <p><span>二．</span><span> 1. personality<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>2. shortage<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>3. majority<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>4. guidance<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>5. percentage<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>6. freedom<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>7. nationality<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>8.discovery<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>9. wisdom<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>10. kingdom<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>11. health<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>12. safety<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>13. temperature<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>14. creature<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>15. advertisement<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>16. criminal<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>17. literature<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>18. amusement<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>19. hardship<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>20. pressure<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>21 relationship<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>22. judgment<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>23. instructor<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>24. dentist<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>25. musicians<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>26. tourists<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>27. conductor<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>28.educator<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>29. curiosity<span>&nbsp; </span>30. novelist</span></p>
          <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><span>&nbsp; 你看到的只是第十章的三分之一的内容，相信已经感受到它的价值了，其实本书真正的核心在第九章，可以保证让你高中学生最怕的完形和单选成绩飞速提升，</span><span>那不仅只是一本书，是成都7中英语教学的集体智慧和</span><span>秘诀体现。<span>这么重要的一本书就</span></span>区区三四十元（<span>奇速英语官方网站沟宝店</span><a href="http://shop63703130.taobao.com/#tc_qz_original=757722345" target="_blank">http://shop63703130.taobao.com/</a><span>）。</span>四川英济律师事务所谢国成律师再次提醒你：<span>每一个前后缀中英文编写整理，每一个举例单词和句子都</span><span><span>凝聚着数位名师心血，请尊重我们的劳动成果，</span></span><span><span>欢迎直接</span><span>转载分享，如</span></span><span>复制里面任何部分</span><span>必须写明下面字样（版权所有，本文转载于蔡章兵主编QQ757722345空间，转载分享或复制必须注明出自《奇速英语.高中英语实用语法（词汇+词类编）》；主编：马智慧/蔡章兵/朱文英；出版：吉林出版集团，否则我们将彻底追究当事人经济赔偿和法律责任。），如果你要更多答案或咨询，请与我们联系。</span></p>
          <div>
           <br />
           <span>那么无论考什么作文，都逃脱不了这本书的24个话题</span>。真正做到以不变应万变！这叫“英语话题作文导与练在手，高/中考高分作文从此无忧! ”
